    },
    {
      "id": "085e79ad42844a4639e083756681d9807f0e174f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2018-05-14 03:22:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nSo I performed the experiment. Using the test program from the ticket (opens closes file 100 times) we can see that every time we run it, the cancel count increases by 300 (on master - before this patch). The remaining locks in lru is 4 regardless.\n\nNot sure why we have 3x cancel rate for every open/close cycle - something to find out later I guess.\n\nAs such I am sure this patch cancellations would work fine as well.\n\nIn fact let me try this patch...\n\nOk with this patch lru_size hangs at 4 still, but number of cancels per open/close cycle drops to 100 which is drastically better than before this patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "7f25cd78bffeeaae29178ad5ac417fd297e3ba8e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2018-05-14 05:48:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIt would be worthwhile to track down what those extra locks are. It's possible we are doing foolish things like getting separate lock bits from the MDS on each open. \n\nIt would also be good to add some tests for this, since we've had several similar problems in the past. Something like your open+close loop and could the different RPC types, and the test fails if it is more than expected.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "f5c643cc5c0c6fa3dc639dded8adb6317d633443",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2018-05-14 15:01:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI did some research into that. Originally I looked into mdt stats for cancels, but it seems to include local cancels too. The client only sends 100 cancels either way.\n\nNow why would server do 2x lock get and cancel is a bit more of a mystery.\nI see there's CW and PW locks with bit 2 and CR bit 8 which is returned to the client",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "1eeeaf643709858150978952cdbcefd47c42796c",
