    {
      "id": "77fca247bbb5da55c940050ac08fda850b6832ab",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2018-08-02 21:40:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nSee also patch https://review.whamcloud.com/32929 which is adding MDS_INODELOCK_LOOKUP only into the trybits.  If that patch lands, this one should undo that change.\n\nThe question is whether this change should add MDS_INODELOCK_LOOKUP into the ibits or only put it in trybits (but always requested, unlike 32929 which only requests the trybits with MDS_INODELOCK_LAYOUT)?\n\nOleg, you should give that some thought on whether there is any interaction with your WBC patches.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
